        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer18244999" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10373733150016108625">Tom Robbins writes one sentence at a time. I read that in an interview once. He has a general outline or story arc for his books but he starts out by writing the first sentence, and then perfecting it. Once he is totally satisfied, he moves on to the second sentence and then perfects that one... and so on. I&apos;m not sure if it&apos;s 100% true but reading his work certainly makes me believe it.<br/><br/>Another Roadside Attraction has always been in my top 5 of all time. Is there a way to mark that? Guess not. O</span>
  <span id="freeText10373733150016108625" style="display:none">Tom Robbins writes one sentence at a time. I read that in an interview once. He has a general outline or story arc for his books but he starts out by writing the first sentence, and then perfecting it. Once he is totally satisfied, he moves on to the second sentence and then perfects that one... and so on. I'm not sure if it's 100% true but reading his work certainly makes me believe it.<br /><br />Another Roadside Attraction has always been in my top 5 of all time. Is there a way to mark that? Guess not. Oh well.</span>
