        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer119308870" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8512704081174461277">Tom Robbins was recommended to me aeons ago by a friend (now an occasional friend). I confess a little disappointment with <i>Another Roadside Attraction</i>, but the depth and range of ideas explored in the book is amazing.<br/><br/>I loved the ludicrous metaphors, the freewheeling insanity of language, the satirical humour and the intelligently argued discourses on the death of religion.<br/><br/>On a craft level, I felt the plot could have used a huge pair of scissors, and many of the characters suffered from having th</span>
  <span id="freeText8512704081174461277" style="display:none">Tom Robbins was recommended to me aeons ago by a friend (now an occasional friend). I confess a little disappointment with <i>Another Roadside Attraction</i>, but the depth and range of ideas explored in the book is amazing.<br /><br />I loved the ludicrous metaphors, the freewheeling insanity of language, the satirical humour and the intelligently argued discourses on the death of religion.<br /><br />On a craft level, I felt the plot could have used a huge pair of scissors, and many of the characters suffered from having the same voice, or the same habit of launching into erudite philsophical treatises for no reason.<br /><br />So with a little strimming this could have been a classic. It certainly packs a mean wallop and sits pretty on the bookshelves of athiests and agnostics alike. <br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="8512704081174461277" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


